	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f104331450182479">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=18002&amp;mid=104331450182479">Focus Stacking</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=18002&amp;mid=104331450182479#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Thu, Jan 23rd 5:03 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=174116"><span id="Scholar">Branaddar</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">495 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.36]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Okay, let's clear it up...<br/><br/>Focuses do NOT stack. They act just like items with &quot;Effect: Haste(Worn)&quot; do... the higher effect will be used in checks.<br/><br/>So if you have these godly gloves, and, say, an improved damage 4 item that only ups damage by 10%, it will ignore the 10% item and do 25% more damage when you cast Strike of Solusek.<br/><br/>The same is true of all spell haste, mana preservation, improved damage, extended enhancement/affliction/etc type effects.<br/><br/>And as a side-note... affliction efficiency, which lowers mana costs, does not stack with mana preservation, though AE does reduce mana costs more than MP does (for the &quot;affliction&quot; line of spells, namely dots, a lot of debuffs and slows)</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=939819 target=akztarg><span style='color: red;'><b>Bransback Balefire</b></span style='color: red;'></a><br/>Monk of <span style='color: green;'>Invictvs</span style='color: green;'><br/><span style='color: blue;'>Tholuxe Paells</span style='color: blue;'></td></tr>
